Movie producer-cum-director Kunle Afolayan is set to feature his daughter in his next movie project. He recently announced his excitement over this project which he has been working on for over six years. The producer of “Naija Christmas” a movie released on Netflix 2021 shared a picture of the daughter costumed for a traditional role alongside his elder sister, Moji Olayiwola on Instagram. He wrote: “The legacy lives on. #Afolayan #adelove”   Nollywood actor, Kanayo O. Kanayo celebrates 60th birthday     Pretty Mike attends party with ladies dressed as animals     Alaafin’s daughter makes acting debut   According to the veteran director, the movie titled “Anikulapo” centres on the Oyo Empire in the 17th/18th centuries and was shot at Ikomu, Igbojaye and Babaode in Oyo State. Movie bigwigs such as Sola Sobowale, Fathia Balogun, Adebayo Salami Bimbo Ademoye, Kunle Remi, Moji Olayiwola and many others will feature in the project. He added: “If you are a lover of art, esthetics, lighting, photography, Cinematography, set design, production design, art direction, props then these images should excite you. We are excited about #anikulapothemovie and @kapfilmvillageandresort is the next film village/ studio and resort destination.” Attachments area